I’m excited to bring y’all on on my journey with @hyundaiusa as I find balance off the court during my off-season! I’m whippin’ the #IONIQ5, and through travel, food, art, and fitness, I’m going to be trying new activities that will keep my routine fresh, and get me out of my comfort zone. 

It’s easy for athletes, or anyone really to get burned out from their normal mundane routines and daily schedule. With @hyundaiusa, my goal is to encourage people to LIVE rather than just EXIST! To try new things, throw yourself in the deep end, spark your everyday life with something to look forward to that’s out of the ordinary for you! 

I’m and adventurer and explorer, and I want to challenge myself for try new feats in my off-season. Join the journey with me! 

#ItsYourJourney #HyundaiPartner

Activity #1 ✔️🎾 in my off- season journey with @hyundaiusa was no joke! I’ve always wanted to play tennis and always admired the players, BUT no one told me how incredibly tough it is to learn! I love a good challenge tho, and tennis was a perfect way for me to find balance of staying active and having fun in my downtime. 

I’ll be back on a court soon! Give me some more suggestions of activities I should try in my off season below 👇🏽

#ItsYourJourney #HyundaiPartner #ioniq5 

📸: @shaunmatos

Activity #2 ✔️🏺 in my off-season journey with @hyundaiusa is something that I’ve wanted to try for a very long time! Pottery was not as easy as it looks, but I loved having to work on my patience throughout the process all while focusing on “controlling what I can control,” aka the clay. 

I found that pottery mirrors life in a lot of ways, and sometimes what we create is pretty, and other times not so much, but it’s all a part of the process of becoming and evolving.  

This day, I created a vase, flower pot, and even a small small coffee cup to fit in my #IONIQ5. I guess you can say I got the “potter’s touch” 😉 

#ItsYourJourney #HyundaiPartner

📸: @shaunmatos

Activity #3 ✔️🤸🏽‍♀️ in my off-season journey with @hyundaiusa and the #IONIQ5 has me OBSESSED and wanting more! Acro was life changing for me, for many reasons, but mostly because I found a new technique of mindfulness 🧘🏽‍♀️. The focus, strength, patience, and grace it takes to execute these poses is high level, but once it clicked, I felt like a superhero! 

I unlocked a new level within myself, and truly felt liberated to continue seeking and elevating to new levels! 

When was the last time you did something for the first time?

Activity #5 ✔️🥊 in my off-season journey with @hyundaiusa: Kickboxing has been on my bucket list for a minute! I’ve always been told about how great kickboxing can be for athletes looking to stay fit and active in the off-season, and when I finally tried it, I understood why! 

The biggest surprise for me was how mentally sharp and engaged I had to be. Learning new footwork, punching techniques, and finding my rhythm was a mental task in itself along with the physical. 

In my head, I was killin’ it, but in reality I probably looked like a rookie 😅. Y’all like the new decoration in my #IONIQ5?
